### Delete the RSA private key from your node

During the bootstrap process, an RSA private key is generated on your node to enable your node to make API calls to the Chef server. The default location of this key is <code class="file-path">C:\chef\client.pem</code> on Windows systems.

If you plan to bootstrap your node a second time, for example, to practice the process, you'll need to log in to your node and delete the RSA private key file, like this (you'll need to open your command prompt as an administrator user.)

```ps
$ rm C:\chef\client.pem
```

